How to execute javascript on Dom Loaded?
To execute JavaScript when the DOM has been fully loaded (i.e., after it is ready for interaction), you can use the following methods:

1) The 'DOMContentLoaded' event:
```javascript
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
    // Your code here
});
```

2) The window.onload event:
```javascript
window.onload = function() {
    // Your code here
};
```

3) jQuery's ready function:
```html
<script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.5.1.min.js"></script>
<script>
$(document).ready(function() {
    // Your code here
});
</script>
```
Please note that using the window.onload event will block further page parsing until your script is run, which could potentially slow down your site. The 'DOMContentLoaded' event and jQuery's ready function do not have this problem.

Ensure to replace "// Your code here" with the specific JavaScript functions you want to execute when the DOM has loaded.
